                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.087,
                                "stop": 29.096,
                                "byte_start": 137864,
                                "byte_stop": 221874,
                                "text": "The Sex Offender Registration and Notification Act or SORNA establishes a federal criminal offense covering any person who one; is required to register under SORNA, Two; travels in interstate or foreign commerce and three; knowingly fails to register or update a registration."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.096,
                                "stop": 34.82,
                                "byte_start": 221874,
                                "byte_stop": 244757,
                                "text": "This provision is codified at 18 USC section 2250."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.82,
                                "stop": 51.578,
                                "byte_start": 244757,
                                "byte_stop": 311839,
                                "text": "We grant the certiorari to consider whether Section 2250 applies to sex offenders, who traveled before SORNA\u2019s effective date, and if so whether the statute violates the Constitution\u0027s prohibition on ex-post facto laws."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.578,
                                "stop": 64.266,
                                "byte_start": 311839,
                                "byte_stop": 362621,
                                "text": "We hold that liability under section 2250 cannot be predicated on pre-enactment travel and thus have no occasion to address the constitutional question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.266,
                                "stop": 74.321,
                                "byte_start": 362621,
                                "byte_stop": 402850,
                                "text": "Our decision follows from the text of the statute. Section 2250 sets forth three elements that must be satisfied and served in sequence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.321,
                                "stop": 89.565,
                                "byte_start": 402850,
                                "byte_stop": 463768,
                                "text": "First a person must be\u201drequired to register under SORNA\u201d, second; the person must travel in interstate commerce and third; the person must failed to register as required."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.565,
                                "stop": 97.094,
                                "byte_start": 463768,
                                "byte_stop": 493861,
                                "text": "The first of these elements are requirements to register under SORNA pre-supposes that SORNA has become the law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.094,
                                "stop": 104.464,
                                "byte_start": 493861,
                                "byte_stop": 523431,
                                "text": "The acts of traveling and failing to register must therefore also occur after SORNA\u2019s enactment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.464,
                                "stop": 111.433,
                                "byte_start": 523431,
                                "byte_stop": 551225,
                                "text": "The statute\u2019s use of the present tense, verb, travels, bolsters our conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.433,
                                "stop": 124.009,
                                "byte_start": 551225,
                                "byte_stop": 601590,
                                "text": "We are not aware of any instance in which we have construed a present tense verb in a criminal statute to prohibit acts that were completed before the statute took effect."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.009,
                                "stop": 142.521,
                                "byte_start": 601590,
                                "byte_stop": 675568,
                                "text": "The government contends that limiting section 2250 to post enactment travel is anomalous because it means that the statute will covers state sex offenders, less often than federal sex offenders or liable under section 2250 without proof of travel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.521,
                                "stop": 160.326,
                                "byte_start": 675568,
                                "byte_stop": 746830,
                                "text": "It is entirely reasonable however for Congress to have chosen to treat state and federal sex offenders differently, give, giving, given, the state\u0027s primary responsibility for punishing state offenders who failed to register."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.326,
                                "stop": 171.887,
                                "byte_start": 746830,
                                "byte_stop": 793119,
                                "text": "The government also asserts that reading section 2250 to apply only to post SORNA travel is at odds with Congress\u2019s goal of locating missing sex offenders."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.887,
                                "stop": 180.932,
                                "byte_start": 793119,
                                "byte_stop": 829273,
                                "text": "Section 2250 however is not a stand-alone provision; many other provisions of SORNA advance this broad objective."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.932,
                                "stop": 199.873,
                                "byte_start": 829273,
                                "byte_stop": 905028,
                                "text": "Considering the structure of the statute as a whole, we conclude that section 2250 serves a more specific function, is subject to federal prosecution sex offenders who after SORNA\u2019s enactment undermine the statue\u0027s effectiveness by traveling across state lines."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.873,
                                "stop": 203.648,
                                "byte_start": 905028,
                                "byte_stop": 920074,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we reverse the judgment of the Seventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.648,
                                "stop": 209.061,
                                "byte_start": 920074,
                                "byte_stop": 941808,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 209.061,
                                "stop": 215.928,
                                "byte_start": 941808,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Thomas and Ginsburg join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
